    "where π converts natural-language prompts l and other inputs based on stored knowledge (in the form of a knowledge graph (KG) here) into an index ID meta and space (or space-time) coding pattern C of the chosen SPM.",
    "Here, the policy function π is constructed as a pipeline, where the natural-language prompts l and other inputs from KG are first inputted to LLMs, and the LLMs generates executable Python code after series of reasoning.",
    "Then, in this pipeline the code generated by LLMs is executed to control the coding pattern C of the target SPM via the Field Programmable Gate Array (FPGA).",
    "Of course, the major challenge lies in representing π due to the cross-modality nature of inputs and knowledge, and the uncertain surrounding environment.",
    "metaAgent's cerebrum tackles this challenge by a \"chain-of-thought\" that is implemented via discussions in natural language 47 of the following four domain experts (see Methods):"
  ],
